HEADWORD: Fluoroscopy
<hw>Flu`or*os"co*py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Examination of
an object, as the human body, by exposing it to the X rays and observing
the shadow cast upon a fluorescent screen; cryptoscopy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fluorous</ent>⟦br⟧
